title: Leopard OS 10.5 Install DVD (sparse image) TehKeyMaster
description:
Howdy, Here today I&#039;ve got an image of the Leopard install DVD. But the nice thing about it is that its a sparse image, so you can burn and use it without needing a Dual Layer burner or Dual Layer DVD. This image will successfully burn onto a standard DVD using a standard DVD Burner. The only down side is that the only program that can properly burn a sparse image is Mac&#039;s Disk Utility built into the OS. So the only way you can burn this DVD is if you already have a working Mac. Any mac OS 10.1 and up will have the Disk Utility program of which I speak located in the Utilities folder in the Application folder.

- TehKeyMaster -
